{
  "text": "REMARK 6: The results of [CITATION_1] are obtained from this theorem by substituting \u03c4 = 0 in [CITATION_2] . Denoting \u03b8(\u03c1) in this case by \u03b8 E , we find that cos \u03b8 E = cos 2 \u03c1. Further, substituting \u03b8 E into (15), we find that \u03c1(R) = \u03b8 s (R), i.e., the optimizing value of the decoding radius in (9) in this case is \u03b8 s . Taking \u03c4 = 0 in (16), we obtain for \u03b8 1 the explicit equation cos \u03b8 1 = (A/4) sin 2 \u03b8 1 whence \u03b8 1 = \u03b8 e . Further, the equation for R * which in general is \u03b8(\u03c1(R)) = \u03b8 1 , now reduces to \u03b8 E = \u03b8 1 or",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "110331201",
